Thanks Brandt for the repro. Based on debugging this, I speculate the following is happening:
The code which crashes is
```
        case _EXIT_TRACE: {
        ....
            if (exit->executor && !exit->executor->vm_data.valid) {
                exit->temperature = initial_temperature_backoff_counter();
                _PyFrame_SetStackPointer(frame, stack_pointer);
                Py_CLEAR(exit->executor);  // THIS CRASHES
                stack_pointer = _PyFrame_GetStackPointer(frame);
            }
```
This causes `assert(executor->vm_data.valid);` to fail. The assert is clearly wrong in this case as we only free the exit trace executor when the data is no longer valid.

I think the correct thing is just to remove the assertion. WDYT Brandt?

